docblock.description: Converts method calls into Twiml verbs.
docblock.long-description:
A basic example:

php> print $this->say('hello');
<Say>hello</Say>

An example with attributes:

php> print $this->say('hello', array('voice' => 'woman'));
<Say voice="woman">hello</Say>

You could even just pass in an attributes array, omitting the noun:

php> print $this->gather(array('timeout' => '20'));
<Gather timeout="20"/>

docblock.description: An important part of any secure Twilio application is correctly performing request validation.
docblock.long-description:
For a complete description of how request validation works, see the Twilio security documentation.

The basic idea is that Twilio builds a string based on the parameters sent to your server and then creates a hash of this string using your account's AuthToken (a shared secret).

Twilio sends this hash to your server as a header in its request.

You can then build the same string and create the same hash as Twilio did, and compare yours to the one Twilio sent to determine the authenticity of the request.

tag.description: the secret key used to sign the token.
